The evidence with the title 'New BLS data show that for all 'chief executives,' the 'average ceo ... ' says Mar 31, 2016  ... New BLS data show that for all 'chief executives,' the 'average ceo-to-average worker pay ratio' is less than 5-to-1  ... Pay gap between CEOs in the S&P 500 and the typical American worker has widened to some ratio like 373-to-1 (as the AFL- CIO reported last year, see “ceo pay continues to skyrocket”). 
